### Test Quick Score Editing Endpoints
### Simplified API - only handles score editing for completed holes

### 1. Check if a hole can be edited
GET {{host}}/api/round/1/holes/2/can-edit
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Update a quick score for a completed hole
PATCH {{host}}/api/round/1/holes/2/quick-score
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 4
}

### 3. Update score for a different hole
PATCH {{host}}/api/round/1/holes/3/quick-score
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 5
}

### 4. Test validation - invalid score (too high)
PATCH {{host}}/api/round/1/holes/2/quick-score
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 16
}

### 5. Test validation - invalid score (too low)
PATCH {{host}}/api/round/1/holes/2/quick-score
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "score": 0
}

### 6. Test validation - missing score
PATCH {{host}}/api/round/1/holes/2/quick-score
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
